@thethingy For those having problem with the audio export (like only video, with no audio), there is a problem with the installation file... which I managed to find the solution for.

If you look at C:\Program Files\Adobe\Adobe Premiere Elements 9\MediaIO\codecs - you will see the file dolby.vca is missing. This is an essential codec for the h264 audio encoding.

1) Now unpack the install folder from this torrent again and go into SOFTWARE folder. Now open the Data1.cab file with a program like PowerArchiver.

2) Search the file list and you should find dolby.vca

3) Extract file and then copy to C:\Program Files\Adobe\Adobe Premiere Elements 9\MediaIO\codecs

4) You'll find now that Dolby Digital codec and sound problems don't happen anymore :)

Perhaps you can fix the installation cab, thethingy? Still, thanks for an excellent release.
